The Los Angeles marathon has a marketing orientation rather than that of a first class 
athletic event.  In only 5 years, it has become the best marketed, slickest, most modern 
and sponsor-driven of the world's major marathons.  The lineup of commercial support is 
impressive.   Mercedes-Benz, along with other sponsors, provides the race with the bulk 
of its operating budget.  The marketing approach makes the race lucrative, but it does not 
give it prestige or attract the world's best runners.  Organizers of the marathon expect to 
increase this year's total purse of $202,520 by $100,000 next year.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d099"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="WSJ870220-0106"
